<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB05564</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT CREATING A MANDATORY FREE SOUP KITCHEN ALLOCATING 3% OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE ALLOTMENT FOR EVERY IMPOVERISHED BARANGAY IN THE CITY OR MUNICIPALITY AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES </td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Defines "Free Soup Kitchen" as a place where food is offered to the hungry for free, frequently located in lower-income neighborhoods.

Provides that the City or Municipality in coordination with the DSWD shall determine the impoverished barangay who upon consultation by the City or Municipality shall determine the frequency of days and hours/day in giving free lunch and dinner for the qualified beneficiaries.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>BAGATSING, CRISTAL L.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-11-20</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Tambunting (000 2020-03-05)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON LOCAL GOVERNMENT ON 2019-11-26</td></tr></table>